    <item>
      <title>Risotto</title>
      <link>https://tomdod.github.io/food/risotto/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 28 Apr 2019 16:46:27 +0200</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://tomdod.github.io/food/risotto/</guid>
      <description>For 2 portions:
 1/4 onion 1/3 carrot 1 glass wine 8 handfuls rice 1 litre veg stock 1 knob butter Parmesan (lots)  1/ Heat oil in pan. Finely chop onion and carrot (no garlicl). Heat oil in pan and cook until soft.
2/ Add rice and cook until seethrough-ish.
3/ Add wine, cook until it&amp;rsquo;s all absorbed.
4/ Add stock 1 spoon at a tine, constantly stirring. Add veg (mushrooms, asparagus etc.</description>
